1
00:00:10,927 --> 00:00:15,807
{\an8}ORION STARS

2
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:18,560
You're kidding me...

3
00:00:19,853 --> 00:00:22,063
He beat the crap out of Kanuma.

4
00:00:22,605 --> 00:00:24,607
He was completely toyed with.

5
00:00:26,109 --> 00:00:28,194
Do you know who he is?

6
00:00:28,278 --> 00:00:29,404
Nah.

7
00:00:29,487 --> 00:00:31,573
That means he's another first-year?

8
00:00:32,490 --> 00:00:34,951
Bofurin is really bad news.

9
00:00:37,078 --> 00:00:38,913
Suo, my man!

10
00:00:39,914 --> 00:00:41,624
You're crazy strong!

11
00:00:43,334 --> 00:00:45,003
Not at all.

12
00:00:45,086 --> 00:00:47,881
Suo-san! Was that kung fu?

13
00:00:47,964 --> 00:00:50,049
Or something like aikido?

14
00:00:51,968 --> 00:00:53,303
I'm not sure.

15
00:00:53,386 --> 00:00:54,220
Huh?

16
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:58,183
My master is also self-taught, you see.
It's apparently a mix of lots of stuff.

17
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,435
Really?

18
00:01:01,478 --> 00:01:03,229
Master?

19
00:01:03,313 --> 00:01:06,733
More importantly, I didn't know
you could get so emotional.

20
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:07,942
That was surprising.

21
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:10,403
Oh, how embarrassing.

22
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:12,989
I normally don't, but...

23
00:01:14,449 --> 00:01:16,993
Sakura-kun got to me.

24
00:01:17,577 --> 00:01:19,579
Don't blame it on me.

25
00:01:19,662 --> 00:01:22,665
But you better go all out when we fight.

26
00:01:22,749 --> 00:01:25,043
There you go on again.

27
00:01:25,126 --> 00:01:27,253
That's all you ever say, Sakura-san.

28
00:01:27,337 --> 00:01:30,215
Oh, but you seem like such a pain.

29
00:01:30,298 --> 00:01:31,883
I don't want to spar with you.

30
00:01:31,966 --> 00:01:33,676
What do you mean by that, huh?

31
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:34,928
Say that again!

32
00:01:35,011 --> 00:01:36,763
Sakura-san, calm down!

33
00:01:36,846 --> 00:01:37,847
Don't stop me!

34
00:01:37,931 --> 00:01:40,517
There they go rubbing off on each other.

35
00:01:41,184 --> 00:01:43,770
It's important to have
external stimulation like this.

36
00:01:46,689 --> 00:01:49,692
Besides, I still haven't forgotten
that you called me silly!

37
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:51,778
Oh, you're so petty.

38
00:01:51,861 --> 00:01:54,864
-You bastard!
-Wait, Sakura-san! Please calm down!

39
00:01:54,948 --> 00:01:57,534
They look like they'll be a great team.

40
00:02:14,968 --> 00:02:16,886
It... hurts...

41
00:02:19,389 --> 00:02:21,099
Ka... numa?

42
00:02:37,115 --> 00:02:40,118
Did they... beat you too?

43
00:02:41,369 --> 00:02:42,245
It's over.

44
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:45,415
It's over.

45
00:02:45,915 --> 00:02:47,375
It's over.

46
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:50,378
It's over... for us.

47
00:02:54,549 --> 00:02:57,719
How nice.
Hey, let me fight that eye-patch-ku...

48
00:02:57,802 --> 00:02:59,888
All right. Next up.

49
00:03:01,764 --> 00:03:03,725
Who's going next?

50
00:03:04,434 --> 00:03:06,644
It's finally my turn.

51
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:17,906
Huh?

52
00:03:17,989 --> 00:03:18,990
What?

53
00:03:24,579 --> 00:03:25,788
Sorry, Sakura.

54
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:27,665
I'm goin' first.

55
00:03:27,749 --> 00:03:29,208
Hey, hold on!

56
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:32,420
The two first-years already fought!
So why do I have to wait?

57
00:03:32,503 --> 00:03:34,047
Sakura-san!

58
00:03:34,130 --> 00:03:36,507
You're going up against Togame, right?

59
00:03:36,591 --> 00:03:39,135
It doesn't seem like
he wants to fight just yet.

60
00:03:44,140 --> 00:03:45,934
Togame is the second-in-command.

61
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:48,645
Normally, I should be
the one fighting him.

62
00:03:48,728 --> 00:03:50,688
You're saying I'm not up to the task?

63
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:52,273
That's not what I mean.

64
00:03:53,983 --> 00:03:55,610
I'm leavin' it in your hands.

65
00:03:58,154 --> 00:04:02,367
It's not like I need you to leave it
in my hands! I'll still fight and win!

66
00:04:02,450 --> 00:04:04,535
Besides, what's up with that slanty-eyes?

67
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:05,912
That punk cut in line!

68
00:04:06,496 --> 00:04:08,873
Do they know each other?

69
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:11,292
Well, it does seem like it.

70
00:04:11,376 --> 00:04:16,214
Hiragi doesn't usually talk about himself.

71
00:04:16,297 --> 00:04:19,217
But, well, it's not really
all that surprising

72
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:21,636
that he knows someone outside of Furin.

73
00:04:24,305 --> 00:04:25,765
Sako-chan!

74
00:04:25,848 --> 00:04:27,725
Good luck!

75
00:04:28,893 --> 00:04:30,270
Sako.

76
00:04:31,229 --> 00:04:35,817
I never thought you'd challenge
someone to a one-on-one yourself.

77
00:04:37,402 --> 00:04:39,237
Did something happen...

78
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:41,030
between you and Hiragi?

79
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:49,539
I can never read that guy.

80
00:04:49,622 --> 00:04:55,962
But it sure is exciting to watch Sako-chan
go up against one of Bofurin's Four Kings!

81
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:59,799
Long time no see, Sako.

82
00:04:59,882 --> 00:05:01,634
You've got a lot taller.

83
00:05:05,221 --> 00:05:07,515
So you joined Shishitoren, huh?

84
00:05:08,683 --> 00:05:10,893
It is what it is, then.

85
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:17,358
I'm sorry, but I'm winnin' this one.

86
00:06:55,998 --> 00:06:59,085
Hey, that's enough talk!

87
00:06:59,168 --> 00:07:01,087
Now, start! Start already!

88
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:29,449
"I'm sorry, but I'm winnin' this one"?

89
00:07:29,532 --> 00:07:32,743
Even now, you're still looking down on me.

90
00:07:33,744 --> 00:07:35,246
Disgusting.

91
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:38,124
The Sako you knew before...

92
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,126
is gone!

93
00:07:41,961 --> 00:07:44,589
I'll beat that knowledge into you.

94
00:07:57,602 --> 00:07:58,561
<i>He sto...</i>

95
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:02,899
-Good job, Sako!
-Get him!

96
00:08:02,982 --> 00:08:05,610
He's pushing Hiragi-san back...

97
00:08:05,693 --> 00:08:06,569
No way!

98
00:08:07,111 --> 00:08:10,198
Way to go, Sako-chan! Keep at it!

99
00:08:10,281 --> 00:08:11,699
Still...

100
00:08:11,782 --> 00:08:15,703
Saku sure is putting up a good fight.

101
00:08:15,786 --> 00:08:19,665
Well, he's one of our
Top Fives, after all!

102
00:08:19,749 --> 00:08:22,543
He can match up to Ragi-chan no problem!

103
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:28,466
Well, I can't get a read on him...

104
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:32,470
<i>But he's been in more fights
than anyone else.</i>

105
00:08:32,553 --> 00:08:36,849
When he joined us, he was punching people
left and right like he was desperate.

106
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:40,561
I mean, I didn't know
he could talk that much.

107
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:43,689
He usually only says yes or no,
a single word at most.

108
00:08:43,773 --> 00:08:45,233
Yeah.

109
00:08:45,316 --> 00:08:49,111
That must mean he has some
strong feelings for Hiragi.

110
00:08:50,947 --> 00:08:52,406
Straightforward.

111
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:56,494
Heavy reliance on strength alone.

112
00:08:57,537 --> 00:08:59,205
Serious to a fault.

113
00:08:59,288 --> 00:09:01,791
There isn't even a trace
of anything interesting!

114
00:09:07,421 --> 00:09:10,007
You really haven't grown at all.

115
00:09:10,675 --> 00:09:13,636
You sure learned how to
run that mouth of yours now.

116
00:09:14,428 --> 00:09:17,431
<i>Before, you were so silent
I didn't even need to teach you</i>

117
00:09:17,515 --> 00:09:20,476
<i>not talk in a fight
or else you'll bite your tongue.</i>

118
00:09:24,021 --> 00:09:25,982
<i>What? He got even faste...</i>

119
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:43,416
Not only have you not grown,
you became weaker.

120
00:09:45,668 --> 00:09:49,422
You ended up this way because
you hang out with those losers.

121
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:52,675
Naive pushovers that only care
about being nice to each other.

122
00:09:52,758 --> 00:09:54,343
-Hey!
-Huh?

123
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:55,636
Not you.

124
00:09:56,387 --> 00:09:59,265
Hey, shark teeth! You! You hear me?

125
00:09:59,348 --> 00:10:02,226
People are lookin' down on us
thanks to you!

126
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:04,770
You can have a weak stomach,
but not in a fight!

127
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:06,314
Sakura-san, hold it!

128
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:10,109
Why are you laughing, Suo-san?

129
00:10:10,192 --> 00:10:12,069
Sorry, sorry.

130
00:10:12,153 --> 00:10:16,741
It looks like you're starting to care
about your friends now, huh, Sakura-kun?

131
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:18,075
Huh?

132
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:20,578
I'm just pissed that
they're lookin' down on us!

133
00:10:22,204 --> 00:10:23,331
If you say so.

134
00:10:23,414 --> 00:10:25,625
There, there. Calm down, Sakura.

135
00:10:26,792 --> 00:10:28,210
Sako, was it?

136
00:10:30,212 --> 00:10:34,091
Hiragi's one of the
Four Kings of Bofurin right now.

137
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:37,595
He's also a leader called Tamonten.

138
00:10:37,678 --> 00:10:39,472
{\an8}TAMON - JIKOKU
KOMOKU - ZOJO

139
00:10:39,555 --> 00:10:43,225
Do you know what's the
other name for Tamonten?

140
00:10:43,768 --> 00:10:45,269
Huh?

141
00:10:48,147 --> 00:10:51,525
Man, it's been ages since
I've taken such a good kick.

142
00:10:51,609 --> 00:10:52,693
That hit hard.

143
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:05,206
But still, I looked pretty
lame right there, huh?

144
00:11:06,457 --> 00:11:08,834
You're crazy strong now, eh?

145
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:11,003
It's like you're a totally
different person.

146
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:14,965
Tamonten is also known as Bishamonten.

147
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:17,885
The god who reigns over
the battlefield, the God of War.

148
00:11:17,968 --> 00:11:20,721
Thanks to you,
I got yelled at by a first-year.

149
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:22,223
Talk about embarrassing.

150
00:11:22,932 --> 00:11:25,184
No amount of pills is gonna fix me up now.

151
00:11:25,267 --> 00:11:28,187
But it's finally getting a lot more fun.

152
00:11:56,590 --> 00:12:00,511
Don't get carried away
just because you're smart.

153
00:12:02,012 --> 00:12:03,389
Know your place.

154
00:12:03,472 --> 00:12:07,601
But I didn't do anything,
and I never got carri...

155
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:09,854
That's what makes you annoying!

156
00:12:13,524 --> 00:12:15,568
Even though you're weak!

157
00:12:15,651 --> 00:12:17,736
Know your place, scrub!

158
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:19,822
What are you guys doing?

159
00:12:34,378 --> 00:12:35,546
Whoa...

160
00:12:36,005 --> 00:12:39,091
This fight isn't somethin'
you see every day!

161
00:12:40,509 --> 00:12:41,969
Wow.

162
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:45,347
Damn, he's hella strong.

163
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:48,934
He's one of the Four Kings of Bofurin
for a reason.

164
00:12:49,018 --> 00:12:51,437
He's famously strong
in our town, you know?

165
00:12:53,189 --> 00:12:55,691
Then he should've gone
all out from the start.

166
00:12:55,774 --> 00:12:58,944
But, well, although he's strong,
to begin with...

167
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:01,572
I think your words got to him, too.

168
00:13:14,793 --> 00:13:18,297
Nice, nice! Sako-chan's so strong!

169
00:13:18,380 --> 00:13:19,590
He sure is.

170
00:13:20,424 --> 00:13:22,426
But if you look closely...

171
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:24,929
Hiragi has the upper hand.

172
00:13:29,141 --> 00:13:30,726
<i>Dammit!</i>

173
00:13:30,809 --> 00:13:33,979
<i>There's no way
you're stronger than me right now!</i>

174
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:35,856
<i>How can you be?</i>

175
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:39,777
<i>You're just living a warm, cozy life
with those people all day!</i>

176
00:13:40,486 --> 00:13:42,321
<i>And yet... why?</i>

177
00:13:43,572 --> 00:13:45,324
Why?

178
00:13:46,784 --> 00:13:50,704
"Why"? They were clearly picking on
someone weaker than them.

179
00:13:51,914 --> 00:13:54,291
Or what? You didn't want me to stop them?

180
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:59,505
If you don't speak up for yourself,
these people will just keep coming at you.

181
00:13:59,588 --> 00:14:01,423
You gotta fight back, even a little.

182
00:14:02,007 --> 00:14:03,425
Can you stand?

183
00:14:09,056 --> 00:14:11,642
Teach me how to fight!

184
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:14,687
Sure.

185
00:14:17,106 --> 00:14:20,234
<i>Back then, you were so strong.</i>

186
00:14:20,317 --> 00:14:23,404
<i>Even though you didn't group up
with other people yourself,</i>

187
00:14:23,487 --> 00:14:26,240
<i>people were still naturally
attracted to you.</i>

188
00:14:27,032 --> 00:14:29,952
<i>I've always looked up to you so much.</i>

189
00:14:30,744 --> 00:14:36,041
<i>I felt so proud to be able
to follow your back.</i>

190
00:14:38,002 --> 00:14:40,880
Hiragi-san, happy graduation!

191
00:14:40,963 --> 00:14:43,132
You're finally going to Furin!

192
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:44,216
Yeah.

193
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:46,343
I'm sure you'll climb up to the top!

194
00:14:46,427 --> 00:14:49,805
A man like you deserves
to stand above everyone else!

195
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:53,893
I'll do anything to help you
reach the top!

196
00:14:53,976 --> 00:14:56,979
Please let me help you once
I get into Furin next year!

197
00:14:57,062 --> 00:15:00,691
<i>I thought you were meant
to be the top of Furin,</i>

198
00:15:00,774 --> 00:15:02,902
<i>back when it hadn't been united yet.</i>

199
00:15:03,319 --> 00:15:06,864
<i>And that I would be there by your side,
watching you succeed.</i>

200
00:15:07,531 --> 00:15:09,033
Hey, Sako.

201
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:13,370
You shouldn't follow me anymore.

202
00:15:14,997 --> 00:15:16,123
<i>What?</i>

203
00:15:17,124 --> 00:15:20,753
I've decided to back up this guy
called Umemiya once I get to Furin.

204
00:15:20,836 --> 00:15:23,631
So I'm not gonna be the top.

205
00:15:24,423 --> 00:15:28,510
Even if you follow me, things
won't turn out the way you want.

206
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:34,892
You have to find a new goal for yourself.

207
00:15:39,647 --> 00:15:41,231
<i>Why?</i>

208
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:54,119
Wow, you did this all by yourself?

209
00:15:54,203 --> 00:15:55,746
You're strong.

210
00:15:57,456 --> 00:16:00,292
Would you like to join our team?

211
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:01,961
And fight me too!

212
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:05,756
Are the people there strong?

213
00:16:05,839 --> 00:16:07,591
Yes, of course.

214
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:08,968
I'm strong, too!

215
00:16:09,051 --> 00:16:13,347
People in our team are devotees of power.

216
00:16:13,430 --> 00:16:15,891
The strong will be recognized.

217
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:19,728
The stronger you are,
the higher you'll go.

218
00:16:20,354 --> 00:16:22,356
That doesn't matter.

219
00:16:22,898 --> 00:16:26,110
All I care about is
fighting strong people.

220
00:16:26,944 --> 00:16:28,988
<i>I'll become stronger...</i>

221
00:16:29,071 --> 00:16:31,907
<i>and defeat him,
making him regret his decision!</i>

222
00:16:33,993 --> 00:16:35,661
I can't lose!

223
00:16:36,245 --> 00:16:39,248
Unlike you, I've kept focusing
on getting stronger on my own,

224
00:16:39,331 --> 00:16:41,417
not playing nice with anyone!

225
00:16:43,502 --> 00:16:44,545
<i>From below!</i>

226
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:58,809
There's no way I'll lose!

227
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:05,733
Not to someone who willingly
bows to someone else!

228
00:17:08,652 --> 00:17:09,653
Sako.

229
00:17:10,654 --> 00:17:14,658
I'm sorry for not meeting
your expectations.

230
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:29,214
<i>No...</i>

231
00:17:30,257 --> 00:17:31,842
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

232
00:17:31,925 --> 00:17:33,761
<i>That's not it...</i>

233
00:17:33,844 --> 00:17:37,765
<i>You don't need to apologize for anything!</i>

234
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:43,729
I've decided to back up this guy
called Umemiya once I get to Furin.

235
00:17:44,313 --> 00:17:46,690
So I'm not gonna be the top.

236
00:17:47,441 --> 00:17:51,487
Even if you follow me, things
won't turn out the way you want.

237
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:56,283
<i>I always knew you were
just trying to be considerate.</i>

238
00:17:57,117 --> 00:17:58,118
<i>But...</i>

239
00:17:58,744 --> 00:18:01,038
You shouldn't follow me anymore.

240
00:18:01,121 --> 00:18:03,540
<i>I wished you didn't say that to me.</i>

241
00:18:04,124 --> 00:18:07,669
You have to find a new goal for yourself.

242
00:18:08,295 --> 00:18:10,422
<i>I know I'm being selfish.</i>

243
00:18:11,423 --> 00:18:14,927
<i>Even so, you've always been my goal.</i>

244
00:18:16,011 --> 00:18:20,474
<i>I didn't care where you were going,
or who you'd support.</i>

245
00:18:21,183 --> 00:18:24,853
<i>I just wanted to hear you say...</i>

246
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:27,648
<i>"Come with me."</i>

247
00:18:53,882 --> 00:18:55,592
Hiragi-san.

248
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:59,513
I'll always follow you wherever you go.

249
00:18:59,596 --> 00:19:01,306
What's up all of a sudden?

250
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:03,600
I've made up my mind.

251
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:06,395
You're a man deserving of the top spot.

252
00:19:06,478 --> 00:19:11,358
I'll always be by your side,
when and after you reach the top.

253
00:19:11,441 --> 00:19:13,360
I'm determined to.

254
00:19:22,578 --> 00:19:23,954
Hey.

255
00:19:24,037 --> 00:19:25,080
You're kidding me...

256
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:27,833
Sako lost?

257
00:19:28,792 --> 00:19:32,880
So that is one of Bofurin's Four Kings,
Toma Hiragi!

258
00:19:34,423 --> 00:19:38,135
Wow, that was truly an amazing match.

259
00:19:42,681 --> 00:19:46,518
Aw, Sako-chan lost.

260
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:48,729
Ragi-chan's really strong, huh?

261
00:19:48,812 --> 00:19:50,314
I want to fight him, too.

262
00:19:53,108 --> 00:19:58,030
Doesn't matter who.
Can anyone drag him down?

263
00:20:01,533 --> 00:20:02,618
No need.

264
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:06,330
I'll carry him off.

265
00:20:17,841 --> 00:20:20,677
Thanks, man.

266
00:20:21,261 --> 00:20:25,057
You don't have to be so careful
with him, though.

267
00:20:26,516 --> 00:20:29,478
All right, thanks for trying, kid.

268
00:20:30,395 --> 00:20:31,897
What?

269
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:36,777
You can deal with him
after your match, right?

270
00:20:38,987 --> 00:20:42,908
Since we won't know what's gonna happen.

271
00:20:46,161 --> 00:20:49,039
What's that supposed to mean?

272
00:20:49,122 --> 00:20:50,707
Who knows.

273
00:20:51,708 --> 00:20:55,671
But well, I'm just talking to myself now.

274
00:20:56,421 --> 00:21:01,176
I don't think doing crap like that
will make your team any stronger.

275
00:21:02,552 --> 00:21:05,138
Aren't you too loud
for talking to yourself?

276
00:21:05,222 --> 00:21:07,432
You're not bad when you try.

277
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:10,018
Good job out there, sir!

278
00:21:10,102 --> 00:21:11,103
Good work.

279
00:21:13,188 --> 00:21:16,566
<i>Doesn't seem like I can just
ask him about their relationship...</i>

280
00:21:18,068 --> 00:21:19,278
Good work.

281
00:21:19,861 --> 00:21:20,862
Thanks.

282
00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:24,324
Your spinning kick is
as tremendous as always.

283
00:21:24,408 --> 00:21:26,326
I'd hate to be on the receiving end.

284
00:21:27,244 --> 00:21:28,412
You're not gonna ask?

285
00:21:28,495 --> 00:21:29,871
About what?

286
00:21:30,914 --> 00:21:32,541
Like who was that guy.

287
00:21:33,208 --> 00:21:35,168
Or what happened between him and me.

288
00:21:36,128 --> 00:21:38,171
Do you want to talk about that?

289
00:21:39,047 --> 00:21:41,425
Nah, not really.

290
00:21:42,217 --> 00:21:44,720
Then I don't want to hear it.

291
00:21:44,803 --> 00:21:47,597
If you feel like it, go ahead and tell me.

292
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:50,976
That's what I want to hear from you.

293
00:21:55,814 --> 00:21:57,232
Got it.

294
00:23:31,827 --> 00:23:34,162
Shisitoren all wear the
same baseball jacket,

295
00:23:34,246 --> 00:23:36,873
so they really feel like a team. So nice!

296
00:23:37,749 --> 00:23:39,209
Not my cup of tea.

297
00:23:39,292 --> 00:23:40,710
What?

298
00:23:40,794 --> 00:23:42,754
Baseball jackets are nice!

299
00:23:42,838 --> 00:23:45,966
Baseball jacket's origin
trace all the way back

300
00:23:46,049 --> 00:23:49,177
to souvenir jackets worn
by soldiers in Yokosuka!

301
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:53,223
That's why many of them have oriental
designs with dragons, or tigers!

302
00:23:55,934 --> 00:23:58,895
Looks like I stimulated something in him...

